<h1><a class="anchor" href="#howtouse"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>How To Boot Your Data Center</h1>
<h3>System Requirement</h3>
<div class="panel panel-default">
  <div class="panel-body">
    Generally X86_64 servers with hardware virtualization support (Intel VT-x/EPT) will do. Same as the SmartOS. [<a href="http://wiki.smartos.org/display/DOC/Hardware+Requirements" target="_blank">Find it here</a>].
  </div>
</div>

<h3>Prepare the DogeOS Live on</h3>
<ul class="nav nav-tabs">
  <li class="active"><a href="#dvd" data-toggle="tab">DVD ISO</a>
  <li><a href="#usb" data-toggle="tab">USB Drive</a>
</ul>
<div class="tab-content dogeos-tabcontent">
  <div class="tab-pane fade in active dogeos-tabpane" id="dvd">
    <ol>
      <li>Burn the ISO to a DVD.
      <li>Boot your server (or VirtualBox VM) with the DVD.
    </ol>
  </div>
